# Capped simple_cluster for the T-floor byte-identity gate (audit finding #1).
# Identical to param/simple_cluster.param but stops early so the new-vs-HEAD
# full-run dictionary.jsonl comparison finishes in minutes instead of ~2 h.
# stop_t caps simulation time -> both runs truncate at the SAME t by construction
# (matched-t, per CLAUDE.md rule 5). The early energy-driven phase exercises the
# solver + cooling + snapshot I/O end-to-end; T never drops near the floor here
# (measured min T = 30000 K over full runs), so output must be byte-identical.
mCloud    1e5
sfe    0.3
stop_t    0.5
model_name    tclamp_byteid
